<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53094j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53094j">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53094j"> 94(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> student of letters</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Early in the twelfth century Robert, earl of Gloucester, acquired the lordship of Glamorgan by marriage with Mabel, the daughter and heiress of Robert Fitz-Hamon. Eminent as both statesman and warrior, Robert of Gloucester, like his father, Henry Beauclerc, was a <mark>student of letters</mark> and a generous friend of literary men. It is no empty compliment that Geoffrey pays Robert when he hails him as &ldquo;one nurtured in the liberal arts by philosophy, and called unto the command of our armies by his own inborn prowess of knighthood&rdquo; and &ldquo;whom in these our days Britain haileth with heart-felt affection as though she had been vouchsafed another Henry.&rdquo; <small> W. Lewis Jones, <a name="WJKA3" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WJKA3"><cite title="source">King Arthur in History and Legend</cite></a> (1914) 65</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
